13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 7-413, is
15 amended to read as follows:
16 Section 7-413. It shall be unlawful for any person to
17 knowingly, willfully, or recklessly:
18 1. Attempt to produce, haul, process, or distribute milk or
19 milk products without an appropriate and valid permit;
20 2. Sell, offer, or expose for sale as Grade A any adulterated
21 or misbranded milk or milk product;
22 3. Sell, offer, expose for sale, or serve milk and milk
23 products which have not been maintained at or below the temperature
24 specified by the State Board of Agriculture;
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2028 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 4. Sell, offer, expose for sale, or serve raw milk or raw milk
2 products without notifying the consumer that the product is not
3 licensed, regulated, or inspected;
4 5. Sell, offer, expose for sale, or serve raw milk or raw milk
5 products without labeling the container of such raw milk or raw milk
6 products to indicate to the consumer that the product is raw or
7 unpasteurized milk and the date the milk was filled;
8 6. Dip or ladle Grade A milk and milk products;
9 5. 7. Transfer Grade A milk and milk products at any location
10 other than a permitted Grade A facility designed and equipped for
11 such purpose;
12 6. 8. Prevent, interfere, or attempt to impede the Commissioner
13 of Agriculture from investigating and enforcing the Oklahoma Milk
14 and Milk Products Act;
15 7. 9. Sell or serve Grade A milk and milk products from other
16 than the individual container, or approved bulk dispenser, received
17 from the distributor; or
18 8. 10. Violate any provision of the Oklahoma Milk and Milk
19 Products Act.
20 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 7-414, is
21 amended to read as follows:
22 Section 7-414. A. The provisions of the Oklahoma Milk and Milk
23 Products Act shall not be construed to:
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2028 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 1. Include incidental sales of ungraded raw milk or raw milk
2 products directly to consumers at the farm where the ungraded raw
3 milk or raw milk products is are produced;
4 2. Preclude the advertising of the incidental sale of goat
5 milk; and
6 3. Preclude the advertising of the sale of ungraded raw milk
7 and raw milk products; and
8 4. Prohibit any farmer or producer from making cheese using
9 milk or cream produced on the farm of such farmer or producer.
10 B. For purposes of this section, incidental sales of goat milk
11 are those sales where the average monthly number of gallons sold
12 does not exceed one hundred (100) one thousand five hundred (1,500).
13 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
17 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE AND WILDLIFE
